
[1]parole

   PARO'LE, n. [L. parabola.]

   1. Properly, a word; hence, in a legal sense, words or oral
   declaration; word of mouth. Formerly, conveyances were made by parol or
   word of mouth only.

   2. Pleadings in a suit; as anciently all pleadings were viva voce or
   ore tenus.

   The parol may demur.
